<HEAD>Bus Crashes In Rio Grande, 14 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EMBUDO, N.M. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Greyhound bus crashed into the Rio Grande
late Monday following a rock slide, injuring at least 14
passengers, authorities said.
   The bus, bound from Denver to Albuquerque on New Mexico 68, went
into the river less than a miles north of the Embudo Post Office,
about 50 miles north of Santa Fe, said a State Police dispatcher
who refused to give her name.
   ``There are ambulances and officers and wreckers up there,'' she
said.
   The dispatcher said the rock slide ``contributed to the
accident,'' but she could not elaborate.
   Fourteen passengers were brought to Espanola Hospital with
injuries ranging from minor to serious, said administrator Grant
Nelson.
