<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Falls, Stock Up In Tokyo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar edged down against the Japanese yen
Tuesday, while share prices on the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose
slightly.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, a 109.64-point
winner Monday, gained 37.42 points or 0.13 percent to finish
trading at 27,794.16.
   On the Tokyo foreign exchange market the dollar, which opened
lower at 133.23 yen, closed at 133.07 yen after ranging between
132.95-133.25 yen.
   Currency dealers said the market was moving slowly ahead of the
scheduled release in Washington on Wednesday of U.S. monthly trade
figures for July.
   An exchange dealer at the Bank of Tokyo said the bank was
expecting the trade figures to show a monthly deficit of about $11
billion, down from $12.54 billion in June.
   Profit-taking pushed the Tokyo Stock Exchange's Nikkei index
slightly lower after an initial surge fueled by an overnight
advance on Wall Street, dealers said.
   The Dow Jones industrial average rose slightly in New York
Monday, but broader market indexes eased and declining issues
outnumbered advancing issues.
</TEXT>
