<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0470</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Florence's Remains Douse Northeast; Keys Brace for Gilbert</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   The Florida Keys braced for thunderstorms and possible minor
coastal flooding from Hurricane Gilbert today and the remains of
the season's previous tropical storm, Florence, doused part of the
Northeast.
   Gilbert was moving westward away from Jamaica and toward the
Cayman Islands in the northwest Caribbean, packing winds of 125
mph. The hurricane is expected to strengthen as it moves across
open waters.
   The rains left behind by Florence were concentrated mainly on
eastern Ohio, New York and Pennsylvania. Rickenbacker Air Force
Base in Columbus, Ohio, recorded 1.99 inches of rain in the six
hours ended at 2 a.m. EDT.
   Showers also were scattered from eastern New Mexico and eastern
Colorado to Utah, and winds gusting up to 60 mph were reported in
Utah's Cache Valley.
   Early morning temperatures were in the 30s and 40s in the
northern Rockies; the 40s and 50s from the central and northern
Plains to the upper Mississippi Valley; in the 70s in the
south-central states and the Southeast; and in the 70s and 80s in
the desert Southwest. Readings were in the 60s in most other areas.
   Today's forecast called for showers across much of the
Northeast, and rain was expected to extend into the upper Ohio
Vally and into central Appalachia. Scattered rain also was forecast
in the central Rockies and Plateau region and thunderstorms
associated with Gilbert were predicted for southern Florida.
   Highs were forecast in the 70s or 80s across much of the nation;
in the 50s and 60s from the central Rockies to the central Plains
and northern New England; and in the 90s in the valleys of Oregon
and central and northern California, the desert Southwest, and from
central Texas across the lower Mississippi Valley and Gulf Coast to
northern Florida and the southern Atlantic Coast.
   At 3 a.m. EDT, temperatures ranged from 34 degrees at Butte,
Mont., to 85 at Homestead, Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 73 fair; Boston 61 partly cloudy; Buffalo 72
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 67 foggy; Cincinnati 72 foggy; Cleveland
69 foggy; Detroit 70 foggy; Miami 83 cloudy; New York 63 cloudy;
Philadelphia 65 cloudy; Pittsburgh 69 cloudy; Portland, Maine 58
cloudy; Washington 69 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 43 fair; Chicago 66 showery; Dallas-Ft. Worth
79 fair; Denver 45 partly cloudy; Des Moines 59 partly cloudy;
Indianapolis 68 foggy; Kansas City 63 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 49
fair; Nashville 73 fair; New Orleans 76 foggy; St. Louis 77 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 61 fair; Anchorage 49 cloudy; Las Vegas 66
fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 80 fair; Salt Lake City 49
cloudy; San Diego 66 fair; San Francisco 58 fair; Seattle 62 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 61 showery; Toronto 72 showery.
</TEXT>
