<HEAD>Three Detained Black Activists Take Refuge At U.S. Consulate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three of the most prominent
black activists detained under state-of-emergency regulations have
escaped and taken refuge today in the U.S. consulate, a lawyer said.
   Two of the three are senior officials of the banned United
Democratic Front, publicity secretary Murphy Morobe and treasurer
Valli Moosa. The other is Vusi Khanyile, chairman of the banned
National Education Crisis Committee.
   A lawyer who has represented the democratic front, Krish Naidoo,
announced at a press conference that the three had taken refuge at
the U.S. consulate in downtown Johannesburg.
   Details of how they got there were not immediately available.
