<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Center Evacuated,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police: Man Sprayed Mace In Shopping Center As Joke</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROSEVILLE, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 18-year-old man told authorities he
sprayed the chemical Mace in three stores at a shopping center as a
practical joke, police said Tuesday. Eleven people were treated for
breathing problems.
   Fumes forced the evacuation of the Rosedale Center nearly two
hours before closing time, police said.
   Eleven people, including a firefighter, were treated at St.
Paul-Ramsey Medical Center and released, said Nursing Supervisor
Joanne Pesek.
   Police said Tuesday that a witness had seen the man spraying
Mace and charges were pending.
   ``We were in the store and all of our customers just started
coughing and wheezing at the same time,'' said Kelli Mulvaney of
Pet Centers, one of the three stores.
   Firefighters used fans to force contaminated air out. The center
reopened Tuesday.
