<1ST_LINE>r a AM-DeliveryRobbery     09-13 0211</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Delivery Robbery,0216</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bandit Posing as Deliveryman Robs Woman of Jewels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROLLING HILLS ESTATES, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bandit stole a United
Parcel Service truck and posed as a deliveryman to rob a woman of
$40,000 in jewels, authorities said Tuesday.
   The UPS driver was kidnapped Monday afternoon while making a
delivery in Torrance, said Los Angeles Sheriff's Deputy Kathryn
Nielsen. The UPS Gardena office asked that the driver's name be
withheld for his safety.
   ``The driver was handcuffed and placed in back of the van, then
the suspect drove to Rolling Hills Estates and robbed a woman,''
Ms. Nielsen said.
   Sandra Del Conte, 44, had just returned home, in an exclusive
area 25 miles southwest of downtown Los Angeles, when the phony
driver approached and pulled a gun, the deputy said.
   ``The suspect, who apparently had been waiting in the UPS van
outside the house, approached her carrying a large box. He then
pulled a gun, forced her into house and handcuffed her to a pool
table,'' the deputy said.
   The robber took $40,000 in jewelry and fled in the UPS van,
which was found a short distance away with the driver still
handcuffed inside, Ms. Nielsen said.
   The driver and Ms. Del Conte were not injured, investigators
said.
</TEXT>
