<HEAD>President Names Olympic Delegation</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDs: Pfautch cq in 3rd graf.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan on Tuesday named a special
U.S. government delegation, headed by U.N. Ambassador Vernon
Walters, to attend the 1988 Summer Olympics as official observers.
   In addition to Walters, Edward Derwinski, undersecretary of
state for coordinating foreign security assistance programs, will
attend the games being held in Seoul, South Korea from Sept. 16
through Oct. 2.
   Also named to the delegation were: James Lilley, U.S. ambassador
to South Korea; Sen. Frank Murkowski, R-Alaska; Donna DeVarona,
former Olympic gold medalist; Sammy Lee, former Olympic gold
medalist and U.S. Olympic diving coach; Roy Pfautch, president of
Civic Action Inc.; Gaylord Virden, an attorney practicing
international law and Ronald Walker, managing director of the
Washington office of Korn-Ferry International.
