<HEAD>One Killed In Shark Attack</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with separate attacks, identity of two swimmers.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shark attacks off Panama City
Beach on Tuesday killed a 38-year-old man and injured a couple from
Georgia, officials said.
   The identity of the victim was being withheld pending
notification of family members, said Florida Marina Patrol Lt. J.
Mike Sweet.
   A McDonough, Ga., couple received minor injuries in the second
attack, which occurred about 45 minutes after the fatal attack at
St. Andrews State Park on the Florida Panhandle.
   Dennis Hadden, 42, and his wife Ann, 41, said they were
returning to shore from a snorkeling trip when the shark struck in
about 4{ feet of water.
   Hadden said the shark bit his wife's arm and released its grip
after he kicked it in the head. The couple said they kept kicking
at the shark until they reached shallow water.
   The Haddens were treated at Bay Medical Center in Panama City
for abrasions and bites on their arms.
   Officials did not know what kind of shark or how many sharks
were involved in the attacks.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
