<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inadequate care for the seriously mentally ill
is ``the major failure of American medicine and social services,''
two private health organizations said today.
   ``This failure is particularly striking since we now know that
the majority of these people can be successfully treated and
rehabilitated,'' said the two advocacy groups, adding that the
major responsibility lies with the states.
   Expanding on a ranking system first used in 1986, a new survey
by the groups concluded that Rhode Island, Wisconsin, New
Hampshire, Maine, Vermont and Connecticut are the best at providing
services.
