early today that the U.S. current-account deficit shrank by 9.8
percent in the second quarter to $33.3 billion had little impact
since it is a less recent reading of the trade picture.
   The current account is the broadest measure of a country's
trade, while the July merchandise trade report will be a more
narrow and recent indicator.
