<HEAD>Polaroid Asks Stockholders to Defer Shamrock Decision Until Later</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The board of directors of Polaroid Corp.
asked stockholders Tuesday to defer consideration of a hostile
tender offer by Shamrock Acquisition III Inc. until Polaroid issues
its own recommendation sometime before Sept. 22.
   Shamrock, based in Burbank, Calif., has offered to buy Polaroid
for $42 a share. The bid values Polaroid at about $2.6 billion.
   Last month, Polaroid's board of directors unanimously rejected
as inadequate an unsolicited offer from Shamrock that would have
paid $40 a share plus a share plus 40 pecent of the eventual award
in Polaroid's patent infringement lawsuit against Eastman Kodak Co.
   A percentage of that potential settlement was not included in
the new hostile tender offer of $42 a share.
