<HEAD>Whirlpool Acquires Emerson Electric Subsidiary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BENTON HARBOR, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Whirlpool Corp. said Tuesday its
KitchenAid Inc. subsidiary has acquired Emerson Electric Co.'s
dishwasher and trash compactor business.
   KitchenAid obtained Emerson Contract Division Inc., a wholly
owned subsidiary of Emerson Electric, for $17.4 million, Benton
Harbor-based Whirlpool said in a statement.
   Emerson Contract's dishwasher and trash compactor manufacturing
operations, based in Mount Sterling, Ky., will become an operating
division of KitchenAid, the statement said. Emerson Contract's
headquarters in Dayton, Ohio, will be merged into KitchenAid
offices in that city, it said.
   About 600 people work for the newly acquired subsidiary,
Whirlpool said.
   KitchenAid is based in St. Joseph and has manufacturing
facilities in Greenville, Ohio, and Oxford, Miss.
 
